comment_regular_data.body:
@bfredl this is only supposed to catch the case where the child tries to mirror the UI of its parent in a `:terminal` owned by the parent.

I agree that the condition in this PR is too broad. For example if the parent does `jobstart(... --remote-ui --server $NVIM)`, that should be allowed if the parent is not displaying the child UI.

IIUC you're suggesting that we could go ahead with this PR, but document that unsetting $NVIM is a way to force it "if you know what you're doing". That avoids needing to detect "will this cause a loop?"
